definition.value: This is an AE which is a medical condition characterized by involuntary rhythmic contractions and relaxations (oscillations or twitching movements) of certain muscle groups in one or more body parts of unknown cause.
This is an AE which preceding convulsion has been observed in sports injuries at the moment of impact where extension and flexion of opposite arms occur despite body position or gravity.
This is an AE which results in avascular necrosis.

This is an AE which may refer to a number of entities: Osteoporosis, a condition in which overall bone density decreases Periodontitis, a condition in which the supporting bone around teeth exhibits resorption.
This is an AE which is an abnormal growth of tissue in bone, traditionally classified as noncancerous (benign) or cancerous (malignant).
This is an AE which the primary symptom of is pain, which often occurs at rest or at night.
This is an AE which is a primary malignant bone tumour, a type of sarcoma that starts in the bones.
This is an AE which is an infectious disease usually caused by Mycobacterium tuberculosis (MTB) bacteria.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which there is a partial or complete break in the continuity of a facial  bone.
This is an AE which is a subtype of the rhabdomyosarcoma soft tissue cancer family whose lineage is from mesenchymal cells and are related to skeletal muscle cells.
This is an AE which is pain syndromes where excessive, acute and chronic pain are observed for which no overt primary cause can be found or surmised.
This is an AE which is a mass of muscle  cells (tumor) that lacks the ability to either invade neighboring tissue or metastasize (spread throughout the body).
This is an AE which is the accumulation of calcium salts in a body  muscle tissue.
This is an AE which is a malignant (cancerous) smooth muscle tumor.
This is an AE which is a medical condition characterized by the inability to control facial movements (such as chewing and speaking) and caused by a variety of neurological disorders.
This is an AE which is a medical condition. It belongs to a group of disorders known as motor neuron diseases.

This is an AE which refers to a range of different signs and symptoms linked to impairment of function of the glossopharyngeal nerve (CN IX), the vagus nerve (CN X), the accessory nerve (CN XI), and the hypoglossal nerve (CN XII).

This is an AE which is any mental disorder that manifests as physical symptoms that suggest illness or injury, but cannot be explained fully by a general medical condition or by the direct effect of a substance, and are not attributable to another mental disorder (e.g., panic disorder).
This is an AE which is a form of inflammatory arthritis characterized by recurrent attacks of a red, tender, hot, and swollen joint.
This is an AE which is a term often used to mean any disorder that affects joints caused by bacterial.
This is an AE which is a long-term inflammatory arthritis that occurs in people affected by the autoimmune disease psoriasis.
This is an AE which is a chronic, autoinflammatory disease predominantly affecting the axial skeleton (sacroiliac joints and spine).
This is an AE which is a major abnormality in the shape of elbow compared to the normal shape of that part.
This is an AE which is a complex, rare, and severe childhood-onset epilepsy.
This is an AE which is a paralytic illness that resembles poliomyelitis.
This is an AE which is a condition which is believed to result from compression of the sciatic nerve by the piriformis muscle.
This is an AE which is a benign smooth muscle tumor that very rarely becomes cancer (0.1%).
This is an AE which is a rare, but catastrophic mechanical complication of acute myocardial infarction (AMI).
This is an AE which is a crisis of a long-term neuromuscular disease that leads to varying degrees of skeletal muscle weakness.
This is an AE which occurs when blood flow decreases or stops to the coronary artery of the heart, causing damage to the heart muscle and it is silent.
This is an AE which is a form of focal dystonia affecting the mouth, jaw and tongue, and in this disease it is hard to speak.
This is an AE which is types of myopathies associated with mitochondrial disease.
This is an AE which is an injury where one or more of the tendons or muscles of the rotator cuff of the shoulder get torn.
This is an AE which is a long-term neuromuscular disease that leads to varying degrees of skeletal muscle weakness.
This is an AE which is inflammation of the perichondrium, a layer of connective tissue which surrounds cartilage.
This is an AE which is a medical condition caused by inflammation of the periosteum, a layer of connective tissue that surrounds bone.

This is an AE which is a hereditary motor and sensory neuropathy of the peripheral nervous system characterized by progressive loss of muscle tissue and touch sensation across various parts of the body.
This is an AE which is a multi-systemic condition characterized by repeated episodes of inflammation and deterioration of cartilage.
This is an AE which is the most forward-facing (ventral and anterior) of the three main bones making up the pelvis and feel it pain.
This is an AE which is the ventral and anterior of the three parts forming the hip bone and has fracture.
This is an AE which is one of the most commonly treated fractures in the United States. The highest rates are seen among the elderly, second only to hip fractures.
This is an AE which is a break in a rib bone.
This is an AE which is different classification of osteoporosis: primary, in which bone loss is a result of aging and secondary, in which bone loss occurs from various clinical and lifestyle factors.
This is an AE which is a general term for a disorder of the development (dysplasia) of bone ("osteo") and cartilage ("chondro").
This is an AE which is a fatigue-induced bone fracture caused by repeated stress over time.
This is an AE which is a region of the abdomen located below the umbilical region and feels pain.
This is an AE which can be classified according to the involved bone into: femoral fracture (in the upper leg)  and crus fracture (in the lower leg).
This is an AE which is a break in the ulna bone, one of the two bones in the forearm.
This is an AE which is caused by entrapment of the ulnar nerve in the Guyon canal as it passes through the wrist.
This is an AE which is a break of the humerus bone in the upper arm.
